data.body:
Hi! I think it would be interesting to add to Openra some kind of building/support power that could provide a shield to buildings or vehicles.
I have some ideas for them:

1 - Building that generates a shield that blocks projectiles:
-This shields has a limited strength and when is hit beyond the limit it would destroy the building OR disable it for some time then it would regenerate over time;
-It could be shutdown by unsufficient power;
-This shield would block projectiles that pass the "Bubble" (I mean it's range);
-It could or not block SuperWeapons. (Ion Cannon and Nuclear Strike)
EXAMPLE: Supreme Commander's Shield Generators
http://img2.wikia.nocookie.net/__cb20070501234236/supcom/images/thumb/1/1d/Cybran_shield_insitu.jpg/400px-Cybran_shield_insitu.jpg

2 - Building that gives an "aura":
-Everything inside the range would receive additional strength (Not healing, shield itself);
-The shield would regenerate itself overtime with a certain speed;
-Allies can/can't benefit from it;
-It can be shutdown by unsufficient power;
-Multiple buildings won't stack;
-The shield building could or not benefit from it;
-The units will only recieve it when inside the range, leaving it will lose it.
-It could be only personal (only the actor itself);
EXAMPLE: Path of Exile's Discipline Aura
http://i1.ytimg.com/vi/op3-qOyjvp0/maxresdefault.jpg

3 - Building with a SupportPower (Shield):
-Choose only one unit to recieve it.
OR
-Target an area and everything inside it would receive the shield;
-It could be temporary or permanent (it can be destroyed) (it would be better to be permanent in RA since there is the IRON CURTAIN)
-Talking about the Iron Curtain, units affected by invulnerability can still lose their shield by taking damage;
-Adds some extra health to the actors, the shield will absorb all damage;
EXAMPLE: Can't find a decent one to demonstrate this.

Note: The shield I'm talking about has limited health and theoretically the IRON CURTAIN gives a "temporary shield that has unlimited heath".

This would be delicious to modders. (I think it would ^.^)
It can be a very interesting feature
Perhaps you can add it in the future. :+1: 

